The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Wider road link added to terminal

 A STAFF REPORTER

 As the Chitpur railway terminal is slated to be commissioned on January 30, the government has decided to widen one more thoroughfare, Dakshindari Road, for effective passenger dispersal.

 Railway minister Lalu Prasad will unveil the city?s third passenger terminal in the presence of chief minister Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee on January 30.

 Following an understanding reached with the railways, the state government is shouldering the responsibility, which includes scouting for funds, of developing the passenger dispersal system at the terminal. The railways is looking after the infrastructure and related matters.

 Canal East Road and Canal West Road have already been repaired and widened at a cost of Rs 30 crore. Work on Canal South Road is on.

 ?One more road along the canal needs to be widened. Dakshindari Road has been chosen to enable passengers to reach VIP Road quickly,? housing minister Goutam Deb said on Thursday.

 The road runs along the northern side of New Cut Canal and meets VIP Road near the approach to the Ultadanga bridge, on the Lake Town side. 

 Minister Deb, CPM leader Rajdeo Goala and chairman of the Assembly panel on transport Sadhan Pande inspected the entire stretch of Circular and New Cut canals.




